cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

The paper proposes a framework for improving the generation of multi-object images using deep generative models (DGMs) by incorporating human knowledge through structural constraints. This involves optimizing a lower bound of the regularized log-likelihood with respect to the generative and recognition models. Given the focus on deep learning, image generation, and regularization, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). However, the paper also deals with computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) topics, as well as neural networks (cs.NE) and graphics (cs.GR).
